parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses electrical power
lights
door locks
and other systems malfunction
the engine upshifts into second or third gear
and the vehicle refuses to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the engine cuts off or goes into low power mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior dash and electronics can cause distractions and malfunctions, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The interior dash cracks
OnStar system stops working
the dashboard lights blink
the radio turns on and off
the door locks lock and unlock
the cooled seats turn on automatically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the key and ignition switch can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition switch while the vehicle is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes are applied but the vehicle accelerates instead
the brake sensors need to be replaced
the central computer needs to be recalibrated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the locking system can cause the vehicle to unlock or lock randomly, leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: The vehicle randomly locks or unlocks while parked or moving
creating a serious safety concern.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Light Illumination and Recall Parts Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag warning light illumination can indicate a potential safety risk, and the unavailability of recall parts can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to airbag deployment failures or explosions, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the passenger side frontal airbag inflator is faulty
the service airbag light appears on the dash upon starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause sharp edges and debris to become a hazard to occupants, potentially leading to injuries or distractions while driving.
symptoms: Cracks forming on the dashboard
cracks spreading or increasing in number over time
cracks appearing in multiple locations on the dashboard.
